## Standard provisions — static vs dynamic

Your current 5.1-5.6 clauses are **universal boilerplate** — they apply to every SOW regardless of what was extracted. That's fine and correct for generic clauses.

But these should be **dynamic** — only included if the data exists:

| Clause | Should be dynamic? | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Limitation of Liability | ✅ Yes | Use extracted `limitationOfLiability` value |
| IP Ownership | ✅ Yes | Use extracted `ipOwnership` preference |
| Security & Compliance | ✅ Yes | Use extracted `securityRequirements` |
| Acceptance Criteria | ✅ Yes | Use extracted `acceptanceCriteria` |
| Change Control | ✅ Yes | Use extracted `changeControl` |
| Governing Law | ✅ Yes | Already doing this in the table |

